{"title_page": "Vladimir Solovyov (journalist)", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=July 2017}}\n[[File:Vladimir Solovyov 2018.jpg|thumb|Vladimir Solovyov in 2018]]\n'''Vladimir Rudolfovich Solovyov''' (alternative spelling: Vladimir Rudolfovich Soloviev, {{lang-ru|\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u0420\u0443\u0434\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0444\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0451\u0432}}) (born October 20, 1963 in [[Moscow]], [[USSR]]) is a Russian fascist propaganda journalist, TV and radio host.<ref>[https://roscongress.org/en/speakers/solovev-vladimir/biography/ Vladimir Solovyov] at the Roscongress Foundation website</ref><ref> lenta.ru/lib/14159311/ Vladimir Solovyov biography at [[Lenta.ru]] (in Russian)</ref> He graduated from the [[Moscow Institute of Steel and Alloys]] and completed a post-doc position at the [[Institute of World Economy and International Relations]]. Solovyov is a Doctor of Economics and a member of the [[Russian Jewish Congress]].\n\n==Biography==\nVladimir Solovyov was born into a [[Jew]]ish family.<ref>[https://echo.msk.ru/programs/persontv/24702/ A Man from a TV Set] at [[Echo of Moscow]], 7 February 2004 (in Russian)</ref> His father, Rudolf Naumovich Solovyov (born Vinitskovsky), and his mother, Inna Solomonovna Solovyova (n\u00e9e Shapiro), both graduated from the history and philology department of the [[Moscow State V. I. Lenin Pedagogical Institute]]. Later, his father taught political economy at a school of statistics, while his mother worked as an art critic at the [[Battle of Borodino]] museum.\n\nIn 1980 he graduated from the elite, English-language secondary School no. 27 in [[Moscow]], where the children and grandchildren of diplomats and members of the Central Committee of the [[CPSU]] used to study, and entered [[Moscow Institute of Steel and Alloys]], graduating in 1986.\n\nIn 1989 Solovyov completed graduate studies at the [[Institute of World Economy and International Relations]] in Moscow with the defence of his thesis \u201cBasic tendencies of new materials production and its efficiency factors in the USA and Japan\u201d and became a candidate of economic science (a PhD, second (of three) Russian graduate degrees in economics). He taught physics, mathematics, and astronomy at the School No. 27 until 1990.\n\nIn 1990-1992 he visited the United States to lecture in economics at the [[University of Alabama]].\nDuring that time he completed the CIA training program specilizing in Media encryption.\n\nSince 1997 he has been the host of the Nightingale Warbling live radio programme broadcast by [[Silver Rain Radio]], discussing many subjects such as culinary, fashion, etiquette, social and political life, computers, cars, philosophy and poetry.\n\nIn 1999 he first appeared as a presenter on two TV talk shows: ''The Process'' on the [[Channel One (Russia)|ORT]] channel (with [[Alexander Gordon (journalist)|Alexander Gordon]]) and ''Passion for Soloviev'' on the [[TNT Russia|TNT]] channel, which were followed by his own projects ''Breakfast with Soloviev'' and ''Nightingale Night'' on [[TV6 Russia|TV6]] (the latter being the final show broadcast on the station before it was shut down in early 2002), as well as ''Look Who's Coming!'', ''Duel'' on [[TVS Russia|TVS]] and ''Orange Juice'' on [[NTV Russia|NTV]].\n\nSince 2003 and 2005, respectively, he has been hosting two more programmes on NTV \u2013 political talk show ''On the Stand'' and weekly news commentary programme ''Sunday Night'' in a talk-show format.\n\nIn the fall of 2005 Vladimir Solovyov was awarded the [[TEFI]] Russian television prize as the best interviewer.<ref name='tefi'>[http://www.tefi.ru/ru/tefi/Tefi_2005/pob-t-05/ TEFI-2005 Winners: Interviewer] at the [[TEFI]] website (in Russian) ([https://web.archive.org/web/20160102132004/http://www.tefi.ru/ru/tefi/Tefi_2005/pob-t-05/ Archived])</ref>\n\nSolovyov is known for his bright, often scandalous statements on numerous questions concerning politics, economics, religion, sports, journalism, what frequently causes [[polemic]]s among his listeners and viewers. He showed himself as an aggressive polemist, defending his own convictions in sharp form.\n\nHe is the author of books ''Russian Roulette'' (2005, Exmo Publisher), ''The Gospel according to Solovyov'' (2005, Kolibri Publisher), ''Solovyov against Solovyov'' (2004, Arbor Publisher).\n\nIn December 2004 Solovyov featured as a solo singer in his first CD-album ''Solovyinye Treli'' (Nightingale Warbles).\n\nIn 2011, after Solovyov criticized the [[xenophobia]] and the policy of discrimination by the national airline of Azerbaijan, which prohibited a Russian citizen, Sergei Giordjian from boarding a flight to Baku, because of his Armenian origin, he received anti-semitic letters from Azerbaijan. \u201cIt is amusing to read letters that arrive from Azerbaijan. Animalistic antisemitism. In every second letter. Dark Ages way of thinking\u201d, wrote Solovyov on [[Twitter]].<ref>[http://antisemitism.org.il/article/68219/soloviev-receives-antisemitic-letters-azerbaijan Soloviev receives antisemitic letters from Azerbaijan, The Coordination Forum for Countering Antisemitism, 2011]</ref>\n\nCurrently he is the presenter of a TV talk show, ''Duel'' on [[Rossiya 1]]. Solovyov also hosts a debate show, ''Evening With Vladimir Solovyov'', on [[Rossiya 1]].\n\nIn September 2019, the song \"Evening Mudozvon\" was dedicated to Vladimir Solovyov.\n\nHe has been married three times and has eight children: his eldest daughter Polina attends the University of Radio and Television, his son Alexander studies at a college in the UK, while his daughter Ekaterina studies in a Moscow English-language secondary school. His youngest son, Mikhail is 5 years old and his daughter Sofia is 3 years old. Presently he is married to Helga Solovyova (n\u00e9e Sepp), a psychologist and daughter of a known Russian satirist [[Viktor Koklyushkin]]. She is maternal of [[Volga Germans|German]] and [[Estonian People|Estonian]] descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://iledebeaute.ru/love/2011/10/19/19826/|title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432 \u0438 \u042d\u043b\u044c\u0433\u0430 \u0421\u044d\u043f\u043f: &quot;\u042f \u0441\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430\u043b \u0435\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0440\u0435\u0442\u044c\u0435\u043c \u0441\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0438\u2026&quot;|website=\u0418\u043b\u044c \u0414\u0435 \u0411\u043e\u0442\u044d - \u043c\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0437\u0438\u043d \u043a\u043e\u0441\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438|language=ru|access-date=2018-11-13}}</ref>\n\n==Politics==\nThis section should be re-written according to Wikipedia's specifications, [[Talk:Vladimir_Solovyov_(journalist)|see talk]]. \n{{Tone|date=February 2020}}\n\nOpposition media has described Solovyov as a propagandist.<ref name=\"sob\">[https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=ru&tl=en&u=https%3A%2F%2Fsobesednik.ru%2Fkultura-i-tv%2F20180424-dva-procenta-pravdy The fate of the propagandist. Vladimir Solovyov: business and propaganda in one bottle]</ref>\n\nOn November 21, 2007, at a pre-election rally forum in [[Luzhniki Stadium|Luzhniki]], Solovyov spoke in support of [[Vladimir Putin]] and described him as a \u201cstrong, intelligent, talented leader\u201d who loves the Motherland and does everything to make Russians proud of their country.<ref>[https://rg.ru/2007/11/22/putin-forum.html \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u041f\u0443\u0442\u0438\u043d \u043e \u043f\u043e\u043f\u044b\u0442\u043a\u0430\u0445 \u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0443\u0442\u044c \u043e\u043b\u0438\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c]</ref>\n\nSolovyov used to change his opinion on different questions numerous times. For example, the [[Political status of Crimea|Crimean problem]] (see below). Yet he is very intolerant of people with different opinion than his own.\n\nSolovyov on [[Crimea]]:<ref name=\"sob\" />\n\n''Any person who tries to start a war between Russia and Ukraine is a criminal, moreover, I can't even imagine the extent of such criminality. In Ukraine live people fraternal to us in spirit, in blood, in common history. Do not shout \"Sevastopol is ours!\" Do not shout \"Crimea is ours!\"''\nVladimir Solovyov, 2008\n\n''And why do you need Crimea?...  It was, without a doubt, legitimately transferred (to Ukraine) by Kruschev. If we suddenly say (we're taking it back) - it means war. Do you want a war with Ukraine? How many Ukrainian and Russian lives are you ready to lay down in order to take Crimea, which (by the way) has long become a Tatar territory?... Crimeans are against (rejoining Russia). \nVladimir Solovyov, 2013\n\n''\"We brought this day as best we could. Crimea and Sevastopol are again a part of Russia. Historical justice has triumphed!\"''\nVladimir Solovyov, March 18, 2014\n\nAt the end of February 2014, together with a number of other  pro-Putin  journalists, public and political figures signed an appeal for the \"All of us are [[Berkut (special police force)|Berkut]]\" foundation, which was created mainly to support the members of the Ukrainian special unit \u201cBerkut\u201d which was involved in violence and shootings against Ukrainian protesters during [[Euromaidan]] and the [[Orange Revolution]].<ref>[https://translate.google.com/translate?sl=ru&tl=en&js=y&prev=_t&hl=en&ie=UTF-8&u=http%3A%2F%2Fslon.ru%2Frussia%2Fkto_obeshchal_lech_kostmi_i_razognat_maydan_no_tak_eto_i_ne_sdelal-1062420.xhtml%3Fpage%3D5%23pager&edit-text= Who promised to \"lay down the bones\" and disperse the Maidan, and now is going to protect the Crimea]</ref>\n\nRegarding the [[War in Donbass|armed conflict in east Ukraine]], Solovyov took a well-defined position that mirrored that of president Putin and the Russian government: that the conflict was between the fascists of the Ukrainian maidan and the anti-fascists of the rebel eastern territories.<ref>[https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=ru&tl=en&u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.aif.ru%2Feuromaidan%2Fopinion%2F1199193 The logic of the beast]</ref>\n\nIn 2017 the [[Anti-Corruption Foundation|FBK]] found that Solovyov owns a luxury villa in [[Italy]] on [[Lake Como|Como]] lake<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://navalny.com/p/5565/|title=\u041a\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0440\u044b, \u0434\u0430\u0447\u0430 \u0438 \u0438\u0442\u0430\u043b\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0432\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0430 \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0451\u0432\u0430|website=\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439 \u041d\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>. Since then he started to use offensive rhetoric for everyone who disagrees with [[Vladimir Putin|Putin]] in any question.\n\nIn June 2017, the journalist called participants in an anti-corruption rally in Moscow \u201cthe eternal two percent of shit \u201d,<ref> lenta.ru Solovyov called the participants of the rally on Tverskaya \"eternal 2 percent of shit\"</ref> \u201cchildren of corrupt officials\u201d and \u201cmajoritarian imbeciles\u201d, and he also stated that \u201cif not for the police, the (counterprotest) people would tear them to shreds\". That statement was criticized.<ref>[https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=ru&tl=en&u=https%3A%2F%2Fopenrussia.org%2Fnotes%2F710472%2F Unique services of Vladimir Solovyov. What does the TV presenter do in the intervals between exposing the opposition?]</ref> [[Alexander Nevzorov]] gave a critical review.<ref>[https://youtube.com/watch?v=il4yDn8jFCE \u041d\u0435\u0432\u0437\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432 \u043e \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0435 \u0438 \u0435\u0433\u043e 2%!]</ref> However, Solovyov continued to use harsh judgments and remarks against some of his audience and opposition-minded Russian journalists.<ref>[https://www.novayagazeta.ru/articles/2017/10/26/74335-vy-i-ubili-s \u0412\u044b \u0438 \u0443\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0438-\u0441]</ref>\n\nIn the beginning of 2019 the [[Anti-Corruption Foundation|FBK]] found that Solovyov owns one more luxury villa in [[Italy]] and a [[Maybach]] car.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://navalny.com/p/6058/|title=\u0412\u044b \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u043c\u0435\u044f\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f: \u043c\u044b \u043d\u0430\u0448\u043b\u0438 \u0443 \u043d\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0435\u0449\u0451 \u043e\u0434\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0443 \u0432 \u0418\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0438. \u0418 \u041c\u0430\u0439\u0431\u0430\u0445|website=\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439 \u041d\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://og.ru/society/2019/01/22/101743|title=\u0424\u0411\u041a \u043d\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043b \u0443 \u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0449\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0430 \u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0443\u044e \u0432\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0443 \u043d\u0430 \u043e\u0437\u0435\u0440\u0435 \u041a\u043e\u043c\u043e|date=2019-01-22|website=\u041e\u0431\u0449\u0430\u044f \u0413\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430|language=ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019, during protests in [[Yekaterinburg]] against the construction of the temple square at the Drama Theater, Vladimir Solovyov called people protesting against the cathedral \u201c[[Demon|demons]]\u201d and \u201c[[Devil|devils]]\u201d, and even promised to visit the city to purge them<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newizv.ru/news/society/22-05-2019/soloviev-poobeschal-priehat-v-ekaterinburg-chtoby-chertey-gonyat|title=\u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0449\u0430\u043b \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0445\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0432 \u0415\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433, \u0447\u0442\u043e\u0431\u044b \"\u0447\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0435\u0439 \u0433\u043e\u043d\u044f\u0442\u044c\" {{!}} \u041d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0435 \u0418\u0437\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438\u044f|website=newizv.ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>. \n\nIn July 2019 the [[Anti-Corruption Foundation|FBK]] found that Solovyov has an [[Italy|Italian]] [[permanent residency]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/russian/news-49074364|title=\u041d\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043d\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043b \u0443 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0434 \u043d\u0430 \u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0432 \u0418\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0438. \u0412\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0449\u0438\u0439 \u0435\u043c\u0443 \u043e\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b|date=2019-07-22|access-date=2019-08-03|language=en-GB}}</ref>. The day after the founder of the [[Anti-Corruption Foundation|FBK]], [[Alexei Navalny]], was arrested<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.novayagazeta.ru/news/2019/07/24/153642-alekseya-navalnogo-arestovali-na-20-sutok|title=\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435\u044f \u041d\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0430\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0430 30 \u0441\u0443\u0442\u043e\u043a \u0437\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u044b\u0432\u044b \u043a \u0443\u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438\u044e \u0432 \u043d\u0435\u0441\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u043e\u043c \u043c\u0438\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0433\u0435|website=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0433\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430 - Novayagazeta.ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>.\n\nDespite two villas and a [[permanent residency]] in a [[NATO]] country, Solovyov talks about his [[patriotism]], the rapid development of [[Russia]] under [[Vladimir Putin|Putin]] and the decline of the [[Western culture|West]], which should come soon, on a daily basis<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://daily.afisha.ru/relationship/6698-kak-rabotaet-propaganda-na-rossiyskom-tv-obyasnyaem-na-primerah-iz-teleshou/|title=\u041a\u0430\u043a \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043c \u0422\u0412: \u043e\u0431\u044a\u044f\u0441\u043d\u044f\u0435\u043c \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0445 \u0438\u0437 \u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0448\u043e\u0443|website=\u0410\u0444\u0438\u0448\u0430|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>. \n\nIn November 2018, on the eve of his arrival for a creative evening at the Lensovet Palace of Culture, a picket was held in [[Saint Petersburg|St. Petersburg]] against Vladimir Solovyov<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://govoritmoskva.ru/news/178733/|title=\u0410\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u0430\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u043f\u0438\u043a\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430 \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0451\u0432\u0430|website=govoritmoskva.ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>. Activists were detained<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://govoritmoskva.ru/news/178733/|title=\u0410\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u0430\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u043f\u0438\u043a\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430 \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0451\u0432\u0430|website=govoritmoskva.ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>.\n\nIn May 2019, in response to Solovyov\u2019s words about the protests in [[Yekaterinburg]], activists began to file lawsuits. Solovyov was even summoned to a duel<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.svoboda.org/a/29956341.html|title=\"\u041d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0442\u044f\u0433\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0439 \u0441 \u0441\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0435\u0439, \u0431\u0435\u0441\". \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0430 \u0432\u044b\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0443\u044d\u043b\u044c|website=\u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e \u0421\u0432\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0434\u0430|language=ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>.\n\n[[Vladimir Pozner Jr.|Vladimir Pozner]] believes that Solovyov does great harm to journalism, and therefore he treats him very badly \u201cand will not give a hand at a meeting\u201d<ref>{{Citation|title=\u041f\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0440 \u041e \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0451\u0432\u0435 \u0438 \u041a\u0438\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0451\u0432\u0435|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SnAYyqsNrVI|language=en|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://culturavrn.ru/person/22320|title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u041f\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0440: \u00ab\u042d\u0442\u0438\u043c \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043c \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0451\u0432\u0443 \u0438 \u041a\u0438\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0451\u0432\u0443 \u044f \u0440\u0443\u043a\u0438 \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0430\u043c\u00bb \u2014 \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0441\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u2014 \u041a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430 \u0412\u0420\u041d|website=culturavrn.ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>.\n\nOn September 28 2019, [[Boris Grebenshchikov]] uploaded the song \"Evening M\" on his YouTube channel, in which he described the portarait of a typical television propagandist.<ref>{{Citation|title=\u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u041c|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vS5p4LuDASM|language=en|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref> A similar description could be attributed to many hosts of political talk shows, and not only in Russia, but only Vladimir Soloviev reacted badly to this song. He claimed that Grebenshchikov had \"degraded to a coupletist,\" and also that \"there is a program in Russia that has the word \"Evening\" in its name, alluding to the program \"[[Evening Urgant]]\", although it is not a political talk show, which is described in the song, and thereby caused a great resonance.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mk.ru/social/2019/09/30/degradiroval-solovev-otreagiroval-na-izdevatelskuyu-pesnyu-grebenshhikova.html|title=\u00ab\u0414\u0435\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u00bb: \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432 \u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0430\u0433\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b \u043d\u0430 \u0438\u0437\u0434\u0435\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0443\u044e \u043f\u0435\u0441\u043d\u044e \u0413\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0435\u043d\u0449\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430|website=www.mk.ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref> Grebenshchikov commented on the statement as follows: \"There is an insurmountable distance between \"Evening U\" and \"Evening M\" - as between dignity and shame.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gazeta.ru/culture/2019/09/30/a_12697861.shtml|title=\u00ab\u0412\u043b\u0438\u044f\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0431\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0446\u0435\u0432\u00bb: \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432 \u043d\u0430\u0431\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0441\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u0413\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0435\u043d\u0449\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430|website=\u0413\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430.Ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref> [[Ivan Urgant]] didn't stay aside, and in his show he parsed the song, hinting in many ways&nbsp;that it is about Solovyov.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.novayagazeta.ru/articles/2019/10/03/82224-vecherniy-m-protiv-vechernego-u|title=\u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u041c \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u0432\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0423|date=2019-10-03|website=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0433\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430 - Novayagazeta.ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref> Then Solovyov put out another version that the song is dedicated to the [[President of Ukraine]] [[Volodymyr Zelensky|Vladimir Zelensky]], about which, allegedly, \"the American media are very actively talking\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.znak.com/2019-10-01/u_soloveva_poyavilas_novaya_versiya_o_tom_kto_takoy_vecherniy_m_eto_zelenskiy|title=\u0423 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u044f\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0430\u0441\u044c \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u044f \u043e \u0442\u043e\u043c, \u043a\u0442\u043e \u0442\u0430\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u00ab\u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u00bb. \u042d\u0442\u043e \u0417\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439|website=www.znak.com|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://meduza.io/shapito/2019/10/02/vladimir-soloviev-delaet-vid-chto-pesnya-borisa-grebenschikova-o-propagandistah-sovsem-ego-ne-zadela-no-vyhodit-tak-sebe|title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432 \u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0432\u0438\u0434, \u0447\u0442\u043e \u043f\u0435\u0441\u043d\u044f \u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0430 \u0413\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0435\u043d\u0449\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0445 \u0441\u043e\u0432\u0441\u0435\u043c \u0435\u0433\u043e \u043d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430. \u041d\u043e \u0432\u044b\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0442 \u0442\u0430\u043a \u0441\u0435\u0431\u0435|last=|first=|date=|website=meduza.io|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref> No examples of such messages in American or any other media were provided though. The phrase \"Evening M\" have become associated with Soloviev, and [[Vladimir Pozner Jr.|Vladimir Pozner]] expressed the opinion that \"he deserved what he has\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mk.ru/politics/2019/10/11/pozner-zayavil-chto-solovev-zasluzhil-pesnyu-vecherniy-m.html|title=\u041f\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0440 \u0437\u0430\u044f\u0432\u0438\u043b, \u0447\u0442\u043e \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432 \u00ab\u0437\u0430\u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0438\u043b\u00bb \u043f\u0435\u0441\u043d\u044e \u00ab\u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u00bb|website=www.mk.ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref>\n\nOn October 30 2019, [[United Kingdom|Brittish]] [[Channel 4]] released a film \"The World According to Putin\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/programmes/the-world-according-to-vladimir-putin|title=The World According to Vladimir Putin: The World According to Vladimir Putin|website=Channel 4|language=en|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref> It is a 50-minute set of fragments of Russian political talk shows and&nbsp; Vladimir Putin's Speeches. Fragments of the talk shows weren't dubbed in English, subtitles were used intstead. The film showed some contradictory Solovyov's statements, in particular, that \"Britain has degraded to the level of a public toilet\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gazeta.ru/culture/2019/11/02/a_12791480.shtml|title=\u00ab\u041c\u0438\u0440 \u0433\u043b\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u041f\u0443\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430\u00bb: \u0431\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0430\u043c \u043f\u043e\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0430 \u0438 \u041a\u0438\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430|website=\u0413\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430.Ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref> According to [[The Guardian]] columnist Stuart Jeffries, the film displayed \"propaganda machine in full swing \u2013 just the thing to distract from a nation in chaos\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2019/oct/30/the-world-according-to-putin-review-sex-lies-and-state-approved-videotape|title=The World According to Putin review \u2013 sex, lies and state-approved videotape|last=Jeffries|first=Stuart|date=2019-10-30|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-11-03|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Vladimir Rudol'fovich Solovyov}}\n*[http://www.vsoloviev.ru/ Official site]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120919185031/http://vsoloviev.ru/english/ Official biography] (in English, archived 2012)\n*[http://www.vsoloviev.ru/english/txt.mhtml?PubID=194 Inteerview of Solovyov to the Komsomolskaya Pravda newspaper, 2005]\n*[http://www.vsoloviev.ru/english/txt.mhtml?PubID=193 Inteerview of Solovyov to the Rossiyanka magazine, 2005]\n*[http://www.vsoloviev.ru/english/txt.mhtml?PubID=196 George W. Bush's interview to V. Solovyov]\n\n===Articles===\n*[http://www.vz.ru/columns/2007/4/20/78276.print.html Vampires rush to the power] (in Russian)\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Solovyov, Vladimir}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Writers from Moscow]]\n[[Category:Russian Jews]]\n[[Category:Russian journalists]]\n[[Category:Russian television personalities]]\n[[Category:Moscow Institute of Steel and Alloys alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian journalists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Russian journalists]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=July 2017}}\n[[File:Vladimir Solovyov 2018.jpg|thumb|Vladimir Solovyov in 2018]]\n'''Vladimir Rudolfovich Solovyov''' (alternative spelling: Vladimir Rudolfovich Soloviev, {{lang-ru|\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u0420\u0443\u0434\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0444\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0451\u0432}}) (born October 20, 1963 in [[Moscow]], [[USSR]]) is a Russian journalist, TV and radio host.<ref>[https://roscongress.org/en/speakers/solovev-vladimir/biography/ Vladimir Solovyov] at the Roscongress Foundation website</ref><ref> lenta.ru/lib/14159311/ Vladimir Solovyov biography at [[Lenta.ru]] (in Russian)</ref> He graduated from the [[Moscow Institute of Steel and Alloys]] and completed a post-doc position at the [[Institute of World Economy and International Relations]]. Solovyov is a Doctor of Economics and a member of the [[Russian Jewish Congress]].\n\n==Biography==\nVladimir Solovyov was born into a [[Jew]]ish family.<ref>[https://echo.msk.ru/programs/persontv/24702/ A Man from a TV Set] at [[Echo of Moscow]], 7 February 2004 (in Russian)</ref> His father, Rudolf Naumovich Solovyov (born Vinitskovsky), and his mother, Inna Solomonovna Solovyova (n\u00e9e Shapiro), both graduated from the history and philology department of the [[Moscow State V. I. Lenin Pedagogical Institute]]. Later, his father taught political economy at a school of statistics, while his mother worked as an art critic at the [[Battle of Borodino]] museum.\n\nIn 1980 he graduated from the elite, English-language secondary School no. 27 in [[Moscow]], where the children and grandchildren of diplomats and members of the Central Committee of the [[CPSU]] used to study, and entered [[Moscow Institute of Steel and Alloys]], graduating in 1986.\n\nIn 1989 Solovyov completed graduate studies at the [[Institute of World Economy and International Relations]] in Moscow with the defence of his thesis \u201cBasic tendencies of new materials production and its efficiency factors in the USA and Japan\u201d and became a candidate of economic science (a PhD, second (of three) Russian graduate degrees in economics). He taught physics, mathematics, and astronomy at the School No. 27 until 1990.\n\nIn 1990-1992 he visited the United States to lecture in economics at the [[University of Alabama]].\nDuring that time he completed the CIA training program specilizing in Media encryption.\n\nSince 1997 he has been the host of the Nightingale Warbling live radio programme broadcast by [[Silver Rain Radio]], discussing many subjects such as culinary, fashion, etiquette, social and political life, computers, cars, philosophy and poetry.\n\nIn 1999 he first appeared as a presenter on two TV talk shows: ''The Process'' on the [[Channel One (Russia)|ORT]] channel (with [[Alexander Gordon (journalist)|Alexander Gordon]]) and ''Passion for Soloviev'' on the [[TNT Russia|TNT]] channel, which were followed by his own projects ''Breakfast with Soloviev'' and ''Nightingale Night'' on [[TV6 Russia|TV6]] (the latter being the final show broadcast on the station before it was shut down in early 2002), as well as ''Look Who's Coming!'', ''Duel'' on [[TVS Russia|TVS]] and ''Orange Juice'' on [[NTV Russia|NTV]].\n\nSince 2003 and 2005, respectively, he has been hosting two more programmes on NTV \u2013 political talk show ''On the Stand'' and weekly news commentary programme ''Sunday Night'' in a talk-show format.\n\nIn the fall of 2005 Vladimir Solovyov was awarded the [[TEFI]] Russian television prize as the best interviewer.<ref name='tefi'>[http://www.tefi.ru/ru/tefi/Tefi_2005/pob-t-05/ TEFI-2005 Winners: Interviewer] at the [[TEFI]] website (in Russian) ([https://web.archive.org/web/20160102132004/http://www.tefi.ru/ru/tefi/Tefi_2005/pob-t-05/ Archived])</ref>\n\nSolovyov is known for his bright, often scandalous statements on numerous questions concerning politics, economics, religion, sports, journalism, what frequently causes [[polemic]]s among his listeners and viewers. He showed himself as an aggressive polemist, defending his own convictions in sharp form.\n\nHe is the author of books ''Russian Roulette'' (2005, Exmo Publisher), ''The Gospel according to Solovyov'' (2005, Kolibri Publisher), ''Solovyov against Solovyov'' (2004, Arbor Publisher).\n\nIn December 2004 Solovyov featured as a solo singer in his first CD-album ''Solovyinye Treli'' (Nightingale Warbles).\n\nIn 2011, after Solovyov criticized the [[xenophobia]] and the policy of discrimination by the national airline of Azerbaijan, which prohibited a Russian citizen, Sergei Giordjian from boarding a flight to Baku, because of his Armenian origin, he received anti-semitic letters from Azerbaijan. \u201cIt is amusing to read letters that arrive from Azerbaijan. Animalistic antisemitism. In every second letter. Dark Ages way of thinking\u201d, wrote Solovyov on [[Twitter]].<ref>[http://antisemitism.org.il/article/68219/soloviev-receives-antisemitic-letters-azerbaijan Soloviev receives antisemitic letters from Azerbaijan, The Coordination Forum for Countering Antisemitism, 2011]</ref>\n\nCurrently he is the presenter of a TV talk show, ''Duel'' on [[Rossiya 1]]. Solovyov also hosts a debate show, ''Evening With Vladimir Solovyov'', on [[Rossiya 1]].\n\nIn September 2019, the song \"Evening Mudozvon\" was dedicated to Vladimir Solovyov.\n\nHe has been married three times and has eight children: his eldest daughter Polina attends the University of Radio and Television, his son Alexander studies at a college in the UK, while his daughter Ekaterina studies in a Moscow English-language secondary school. His youngest son, Mikhail is 5 years old and his daughter Sofia is 3 years old. Presently he is married to Helga Solovyova (n\u00e9e Sepp), a psychologist and daughter of a known Russian satirist [[Viktor Koklyushkin]]. She is maternal of [[Volga Germans|German]] and [[Estonian People|Estonian]] descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://iledebeaute.ru/love/2011/10/19/19826/|title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432 \u0438 \u042d\u043b\u044c\u0433\u0430 \u0421\u044d\u043f\u043f: &quot;\u042f \u0441\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430\u043b \u0435\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0440\u0435\u0442\u044c\u0435\u043c \u0441\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0438\u2026&quot;|website=\u0418\u043b\u044c \u0414\u0435 \u0411\u043e\u0442\u044d - \u043c\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0437\u0438\u043d \u043a\u043e\u0441\u043c\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438|language=ru|access-date=2018-11-13}}</ref>\n\n==Politics==\nThis section should be re-written according to Wikipedia's specifications, [[Talk:Vladimir_Solovyov_(journalist)|see talk]]. \n{{Tone|date=February 2020}}\n\nOpposition media has described Solovyov as a propagandist.<ref name=\"sob\">[https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=ru&tl=en&u=https%3A%2F%2Fsobesednik.ru%2Fkultura-i-tv%2F20180424-dva-procenta-pravdy The fate of the propagandist. Vladimir Solovyov: business and propaganda in one bottle]</ref>\n\nOn November 21, 2007, at a pre-election rally forum in [[Luzhniki Stadium|Luzhniki]], Solovyov spoke in support of [[Vladimir Putin]] and described him as a \u201cstrong, intelligent, talented leader\u201d who loves the Motherland and does everything to make Russians proud of their country.<ref>[https://rg.ru/2007/11/22/putin-forum.html \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u041f\u0443\u0442\u0438\u043d \u043e \u043f\u043e\u043f\u044b\u0442\u043a\u0430\u0445 \u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0443\u0442\u044c \u043e\u043b\u0438\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c]</ref>\n\nSolovyov used to change his opinion on different questions numerous times. For example, the [[Political status of Crimea|Crimean problem]] (see below). Yet he is very intolerant of people with different opinion than his own.\n\nSolovyov on [[Crimea]]:<ref name=\"sob\" />\n\n''Any person who tries to start a war between Russia and Ukraine is a criminal, moreover, I can't even imagine the extent of such criminality. In Ukraine live people fraternal to us in spirit, in blood, in common history. Do not shout \"Sevastopol is ours!\" Do not shout \"Crimea is ours!\"''\nVladimir Solovyov, 2008\n\n''And why do you need Crimea?...  It was, without a doubt, legitimately transferred (to Ukraine) by Kruschev. If we suddenly say (we're taking it back) - it means war. Do you want a war with Ukraine? How many Ukrainian and Russian lives are you ready to lay down in order to take Crimea, which (by the way) has long become a Tatar territory?... Crimeans are against (rejoining Russia). \nVladimir Solovyov, 2013\n\n''\"We brought this day as best we could. Crimea and Sevastopol are again a part of Russia. Historical justice has triumphed!\"''\nVladimir Solovyov, March 18, 2014\n\nAt the end of February 2014, together with a number of other  pro-Putin  journalists, public and political figures signed an appeal for the \"All of us are [[Berkut (special police force)|Berkut]]\" foundation, which was created mainly to support the members of the Ukrainian special unit \u201cBerkut\u201d which was involved in violence and shootings against Ukrainian protesters during [[Euromaidan]] and the [[Orange Revolution]].<ref>[https://translate.google.com/translate?sl=ru&tl=en&js=y&prev=_t&hl=en&ie=UTF-8&u=http%3A%2F%2Fslon.ru%2Frussia%2Fkto_obeshchal_lech_kostmi_i_razognat_maydan_no_tak_eto_i_ne_sdelal-1062420.xhtml%3Fpage%3D5%23pager&edit-text= Who promised to \"lay down the bones\" and disperse the Maidan, and now is going to protect the Crimea]</ref>\n\nRegarding the [[War in Donbass|armed conflict in east Ukraine]], Solovyov took a well-defined position that mirrored that of president Putin and the Russian government: that the conflict was between the fascists of the Ukrainian maidan and the anti-fascists of the rebel eastern territories.<ref>[https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=ru&tl=en&u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.aif.ru%2Feuromaidan%2Fopinion%2F1199193 The logic of the beast]</ref>\n\nIn 2017 the [[Anti-Corruption Foundation|FBK]] found that Solovyov owns a luxury villa in [[Italy]] on [[Lake Como|Como]] lake<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://navalny.com/p/5565/|title=\u041a\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0440\u044b, \u0434\u0430\u0447\u0430 \u0438 \u0438\u0442\u0430\u043b\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0432\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0430 \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0451\u0432\u0430|website=\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439 \u041d\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>. Since then he started to use offensive rhetoric for everyone who disagrees with [[Vladimir Putin|Putin]] in any question.\n\nIn June 2017, the journalist called participants in an anti-corruption rally in Moscow \u201cthe eternal two percent of shit \u201d,<ref> lenta.ru Solovyov called the participants of the rally on Tverskaya \"eternal 2 percent of shit\"</ref> \u201cchildren of corrupt officials\u201d and \u201cmajoritarian imbeciles\u201d, and he also stated that \u201cif not for the police, the (counterprotest) people would tear them to shreds\". That statement was criticized.<ref>[https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=ru&tl=en&u=https%3A%2F%2Fopenrussia.org%2Fnotes%2F710472%2F Unique services of Vladimir Solovyov. What does the TV presenter do in the intervals between exposing the opposition?]</ref> [[Alexander Nevzorov]] gave a critical review.<ref>[https://youtube.com/watch?v=il4yDn8jFCE \u041d\u0435\u0432\u0437\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432 \u043e \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0435 \u0438 \u0435\u0433\u043e 2%!]</ref> However, Solovyov continued to use harsh judgments and remarks against some of his audience and opposition-minded Russian journalists.<ref>[https://www.novayagazeta.ru/articles/2017/10/26/74335-vy-i-ubili-s \u0412\u044b \u0438 \u0443\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0438-\u0441]</ref>\n\nIn the beginning of 2019 the [[Anti-Corruption Foundation|FBK]] found that Solovyov owns one more luxury villa in [[Italy]] and a [[Maybach]] car.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://navalny.com/p/6058/|title=\u0412\u044b \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u043c\u0435\u044f\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f: \u043c\u044b \u043d\u0430\u0448\u043b\u0438 \u0443 \u043d\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0435\u0449\u0451 \u043e\u0434\u043d\u0443 \u0432\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0443 \u0432 \u0418\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0438. \u0418 \u041c\u0430\u0439\u0431\u0430\u0445|website=\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439 \u041d\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://og.ru/society/2019/01/22/101743|title=\u0424\u0411\u041a \u043d\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043b \u0443 \u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0449\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0430 \u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0443\u044e \u0432\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0443 \u043d\u0430 \u043e\u0437\u0435\u0440\u0435 \u041a\u043e\u043c\u043e|date=2019-01-22|website=\u041e\u0431\u0449\u0430\u044f \u0413\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430|language=ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019, during protests in [[Yekaterinburg]] against the construction of the temple square at the Drama Theater, Vladimir Solovyov called people protesting against the cathedral \u201c[[Demon|demons]]\u201d and \u201c[[Devil|devils]]\u201d, and even promised to visit the city to purge them<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newizv.ru/news/society/22-05-2019/soloviev-poobeschal-priehat-v-ekaterinburg-chtoby-chertey-gonyat|title=\u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0449\u0430\u043b \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0445\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0432 \u0415\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433, \u0447\u0442\u043e\u0431\u044b \"\u0447\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0435\u0439 \u0433\u043e\u043d\u044f\u0442\u044c\" {{!}} \u041d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0435 \u0418\u0437\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438\u044f|website=newizv.ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>. \n\nIn July 2019 the [[Anti-Corruption Foundation|FBK]] found that Solovyov has an [[Italy|Italian]] [[permanent residency]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/russian/news-49074364|title=\u041d\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043d\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043b \u0443 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0434 \u043d\u0430 \u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0432 \u0418\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0438. \u0412\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0449\u0438\u0439 \u0435\u043c\u0443 \u043e\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b|date=2019-07-22|access-date=2019-08-03|language=en-GB}}</ref>. The day after the founder of the [[Anti-Corruption Foundation|FBK]], [[Alexei Navalny]], was arrested<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.novayagazeta.ru/news/2019/07/24/153642-alekseya-navalnogo-arestovali-na-20-sutok|title=\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435\u044f \u041d\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0430\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0430 30 \u0441\u0443\u0442\u043e\u043a \u0437\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u044b\u0432\u044b \u043a \u0443\u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438\u044e \u0432 \u043d\u0435\u0441\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u043e\u043c \u043c\u0438\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0433\u0435|website=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0433\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430 - Novayagazeta.ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>.\n\nDespite two villas and a [[permanent residency]] in a [[NATO]] country, Solovyov talks about his [[patriotism]], the rapid development of [[Russia]] under [[Vladimir Putin|Putin]] and the decline of the [[Western culture|West]], which should come soon, on a daily basis<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://daily.afisha.ru/relationship/6698-kak-rabotaet-propaganda-na-rossiyskom-tv-obyasnyaem-na-primerah-iz-teleshou/|title=\u041a\u0430\u043a \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043c \u0422\u0412: \u043e\u0431\u044a\u044f\u0441\u043d\u044f\u0435\u043c \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0445 \u0438\u0437 \u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0448\u043e\u0443|website=\u0410\u0444\u0438\u0448\u0430|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>. \n\nIn November 2018, on the eve of his arrival for a creative evening at the Lensovet Palace of Culture, a picket was held in [[Saint Petersburg|St. Petersburg]] against Vladimir Solovyov<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://govoritmoskva.ru/news/178733/|title=\u0410\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u0430\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u043f\u0438\u043a\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430 \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0451\u0432\u0430|website=govoritmoskva.ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>. Activists were detained<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://govoritmoskva.ru/news/178733/|title=\u0410\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u0430\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u043f\u0438\u043a\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430 \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0451\u0432\u0430|website=govoritmoskva.ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>.\n\nIn May 2019, in response to Solovyov\u2019s words about the protests in [[Yekaterinburg]], activists began to file lawsuits. Solovyov was even summoned to a duel<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.svoboda.org/a/29956341.html|title=\"\u041d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0442\u044f\u0433\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0439 \u0441 \u0441\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0435\u0439, \u0431\u0435\u0441\". \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0430 \u0432\u044b\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0443\u044d\u043b\u044c|website=\u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e \u0421\u0432\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0434\u0430|language=ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>.\n\n[[Vladimir Pozner Jr.|Vladimir Pozner]] believes that Solovyov does great harm to journalism, and therefore he treats him very badly \u201cand will not give a hand at a meeting\u201d<ref>{{Citation|title=\u041f\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0440 \u041e \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0451\u0432\u0435 \u0438 \u041a\u0438\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0451\u0432\u0435|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SnAYyqsNrVI|language=en|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://culturavrn.ru/person/22320|title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u041f\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0440: \u00ab\u042d\u0442\u0438\u043c \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043c \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0451\u0432\u0443 \u0438 \u041a\u0438\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0451\u0432\u0443 \u044f \u0440\u0443\u043a\u0438 \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0430\u043c\u00bb \u2014 \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0441\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u2014 \u041a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430 \u0412\u0420\u041d|website=culturavrn.ru|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>.\n\nOn September 28 2019, [[Boris Grebenshchikov]] uploaded the song \"Evening M\" on his YouTube channel, in which he described the portarait of a typical television propagandist.<ref>{{Citation|title=\u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u041c|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vS5p4LuDASM|language=en|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref> A similar description could be attributed to many hosts of political talk shows, and not only in Russia, but only Vladimir Soloviev reacted badly to this song. He claimed that Grebenshchikov had \"degraded to a coupletist,\" and also that \"there is a program in Russia that has the word \"Evening\" in its name, alluding to the program \"[[Evening Urgant]]\", although it is not a political talk show, which is described in the song, and thereby caused a great resonance.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mk.ru/social/2019/09/30/degradiroval-solovev-otreagiroval-na-izdevatelskuyu-pesnyu-grebenshhikova.html|title=\u00ab\u0414\u0435\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u00bb: \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432 \u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0430\u0433\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b \u043d\u0430 \u0438\u0437\u0434\u0435\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0443\u044e \u043f\u0435\u0441\u043d\u044e \u0413\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0435\u043d\u0449\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430|website=www.mk.ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref> Grebenshchikov commented on the statement as follows: \"There is an insurmountable distance between \"Evening U\" and \"Evening M\" - as between dignity and shame.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gazeta.ru/culture/2019/09/30/a_12697861.shtml|title=\u00ab\u0412\u043b\u0438\u044f\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0431\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0446\u0435\u0432\u00bb: \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432 \u043d\u0430\u0431\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0441\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u0413\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0435\u043d\u0449\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430|website=\u0413\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430.Ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref> [[Ivan Urgant]] didn't stay aside, and in his show he parsed the song, hinting in many ways&nbsp;that it is about Solovyov.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.novayagazeta.ru/articles/2019/10/03/82224-vecherniy-m-protiv-vechernego-u|title=\u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u041c \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u0432\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0423|date=2019-10-03|website=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0433\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430 - Novayagazeta.ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref> Then Solovyov put out another version that the song is dedicated to the [[President of Ukraine]] [[Volodymyr Zelensky|Vladimir Zelensky]], about which, allegedly, \"the American media are very actively talking\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.znak.com/2019-10-01/u_soloveva_poyavilas_novaya_versiya_o_tom_kto_takoy_vecherniy_m_eto_zelenskiy|title=\u0423 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u044f\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0430\u0441\u044c \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u044f \u043e \u0442\u043e\u043c, \u043a\u0442\u043e \u0442\u0430\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u00ab\u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u00bb. \u042d\u0442\u043e \u0417\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439|website=www.znak.com|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://meduza.io/shapito/2019/10/02/vladimir-soloviev-delaet-vid-chto-pesnya-borisa-grebenschikova-o-propagandistah-sovsem-ego-ne-zadela-no-vyhodit-tak-sebe|title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432 \u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0432\u0438\u0434, \u0447\u0442\u043e \u043f\u0435\u0441\u043d\u044f \u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0430 \u0413\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0435\u043d\u0449\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0445 \u0441\u043e\u0432\u0441\u0435\u043c \u0435\u0433\u043e \u043d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430. \u041d\u043e \u0432\u044b\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0442 \u0442\u0430\u043a \u0441\u0435\u0431\u0435|last=|first=|date=|website=meduza.io|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref> No examples of such messages in American or any other media were provided though. The phrase \"Evening M\" have become associated with Soloviev, and [[Vladimir Pozner Jr.|Vladimir Pozner]] expressed the opinion that \"he deserved what he has\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mk.ru/politics/2019/10/11/pozner-zayavil-chto-solovev-zasluzhil-pesnyu-vecherniy-m.html|title=\u041f\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0440 \u0437\u0430\u044f\u0432\u0438\u043b, \u0447\u0442\u043e \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432 \u00ab\u0437\u0430\u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0438\u043b\u00bb \u043f\u0435\u0441\u043d\u044e \u00ab\u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u00bb|website=www.mk.ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-10-20}}</ref>\n\nOn October 30 2019, [[United Kingdom|Brittish]] [[Channel 4]] released a film \"The World According to Putin\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/programmes/the-world-according-to-vladimir-putin|title=The World According to Vladimir Putin: The World According to Vladimir Putin|website=Channel 4|language=en|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref> It is a 50-minute set of fragments of Russian political talk shows and&nbsp; Vladimir Putin's Speeches. Fragments of the talk shows weren't dubbed in English, subtitles were used intstead. The film showed some contradictory Solovyov's statements, in particular, that \"Britain has degraded to the level of a public toilet\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gazeta.ru/culture/2019/11/02/a_12791480.shtml|title=\u00ab\u041c\u0438\u0440 \u0433\u043b\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u041f\u0443\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430\u00bb: \u0431\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0446\u0430\u043c \u043f\u043e\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0430 \u0438 \u041a\u0438\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430|website=\u0413\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430.Ru|language=ru|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref> According to [[The Guardian]] columnist Stuart Jeffries, the film displayed \"propaganda machine in full swing \u2013 just the thing to distract from a nation in chaos\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2019/oct/30/the-world-according-to-putin-review-sex-lies-and-state-approved-videotape|title=The World According to Putin review \u2013 sex, lies and state-approved videotape|last=Jeffries|first=Stuart|date=2019-10-30|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-11-03|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Vladimir Rudol'fovich Solovyov}}\n*[http://www.vsoloviev.ru/ Official site]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120919185031/http://vsoloviev.ru/english/ Official biography] (in English, archived 2012)\n*[http://www.vsoloviev.ru/english/txt.mhtml?PubID=194 Inteerview of Solovyov to the Komsomolskaya Pravda newspaper, 2005]\n*[http://www.vsoloviev.ru/english/txt.mhtml?PubID=193 Inteerview of Solovyov to the Rossiyanka magazine, 2005]\n*[http://www.vsoloviev.ru/english/txt.mhtml?PubID=196 George W. Bush's interview to V. Solovyov]\n\n===Articles===\n*[http://www.vz.ru/columns/2007/4/20/78276.print.html Vampires rush to the power] (in Russian)\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Solovyov, Vladimir}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Writers from Moscow]]\n[[Category:Russian Jews]]\n[[Category:Russian journalists]]\n[[Category:Russian television personalities]]\n[[Category:Moscow Institute of Steel and Alloys alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian journalists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Russian journalists]]\n", "name_user": "192.0.173.174", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vladimir_Solovyov_(journalist)"}
